SIMPLE: charlie
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Charlie
<hw>Char"lie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
familiar nickname or substitute for <xex>Charles</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A night watchman; -- an old name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A short, pointed beard, like that worn by Charles
I.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>As a proper name, a fox; -- so called in fables and
familiar literature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Charlock</ent>⟦br⟧
